cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper proposes a new architecture for deep neural networks that addresses the vanishing gradient problem. The paper focuses on the performance of the proposed architecture on two standard datasets, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed architecture for image classification (cs.CV), and the architecture itself involves a combination of sublayers (cs.AI) that are volume preserving (cs.SI).
